msg.content:
Based on the most recent data and my research, here are the current owners of the top 5 most-visited websites:

1. Google.com - Owned by Alphabet Inc., which is Google's parent company since 2015
2. YouTube.com - Also owned by Alphabet Inc. (Google acquired YouTube in 2006)
3. Facebook.com - Owned by Meta Platforms, Inc. (formerly Facebook, Inc.)
4. Instagram.com - Also owned by Meta Platforms, Inc. (Facebook acquired Instagram in 2012)
5. Twitter.com - Owned by X Corp., controlled by Elon Musk (who acquired Twitter in October 2022)

It's worth noting that while these rankings can fluctuate, these websites have consistently remained among the most visited globally. The ownership information is current as of 2023, with the most significant recent change being Twitter's acquisition by Elon Musk and its subsequent rebranding to X, though the twitter.com domain remains one of the most visited websites.
